<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/8827387-dr-g-p"><img alt="" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/m_100x100-c7bfe730633c9983e27caaa66a8e244a.png" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/8827387-dr-g-p">Dr. G.P.</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">This is all imagination but very cleverly linked to some Hindu Gods. It is one&apos;s guess whether the majority likes it or not but the story has been cat<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">This is all imagination but very cleverly linked to some Hindu Gods. It is one's guess whether the majority likes it or not but the story has been catching. One remembers the related God at every step. It is good none of the Gods has been downgraded in the name of fiction.<br /><br />Stories of Gods are also imagination as they are without any scientific basis. In this way there are no facts but all fiction.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
